    "modules": [
      {
        "name": "SwiftUI"
      }
    ],
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Reducing view modifier maintenance"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To create consistent views, you might reuse the same view modifier or group of modifiers repeatedly across your views.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For example, you might apply the same font and foreground color to many text instances throughout your app, so they all match.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Unfortunately, this can lead to maintenance challenges, because even a small change in format, like a different font size, requires changes in many different parts of your code.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To avoid this overhead, collect a set of modifiers into a single location using an instance of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/ViewModifier",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Then, extend the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/View",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol with a method that uses your modifier, making it easy to use and understand.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Collecting the modifiers together provides a single location to update when you want to change them.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-a-custom-view-modifier",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create a custom view modifier",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you create your custom modifier, name it to reflect the purpose of the collection.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For example, if you repeatedly apply the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Font/caption",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " font style and a secondary color scheme to views to represent a secondary styling, collect them together as ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CaptionTextFormat",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ":",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "struct CaptionTextFormat: ViewModifier {",
            "    func body(content: Content) -> some View {",
            "        content",
            "            .font(.caption)",
            "            .foregroundColor(.secondary)",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Apply your modifier using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/View/modifier(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The following code applies the above example to a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Text",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " instance:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "Text(\"Some additional information...\")",
            "    .modifier(CaptionTextFormat())"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Extend-the-view-protocol-to-provide-fluent-modifier-access",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Extend the view protocol to provide fluent modifier access",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To make your custom view modifier conveniently accessible, extend the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/View",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol with a function that applies your modifier:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "extension View {",
            "    func captionTextFormat() -> some View {",
            "        modifier(CaptionTextFormat())",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Apply the modifier to a text view by including this extension:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "Text(\"Some additional information...\")",
            "    .captionTextFormat()"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
